usage: pubs [-h] [--version]
            {init,conf,add,rename,remove,list,doc,tag,note,export,import,websearch,edit}
            ...

research papers repository

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --version             show program's version number and exit

valid commands:
  {init,conf,add,rename,remove,list,doc,tag,note,export,import,websearch,edit}
    init                initialize the pubs directory
    conf                open the configuration in an editor
    add                 add a paper to the repository
    rename              rename the citekey of a repository
    remove              removes a publication
    list                list papers
    doc                 manage the document relating to a publication
    tag                 add, remove and show tags
    note                edit the note attached to a paper
    export              export bibliography
    import              import paper(s) to the repository
    websearch           launch a search on Google Scholar
    edit                open the paper bibliographic file in an editor
